 BEIJING, Dec. 2 (Xinhua) -- In January 2021, 42 members of China's 36th batch of medical aid team to Sudan took off from China and landed in the East African country. The team arrived at a critical time amid severe social instability, economic depression, and a lack of medical and health resources. Moreover, Sudan was under enormous pressure to prevent and contain the COVID-19. Upon their arrival, the team adjusted themselves mentally and physically and then started their work. Despite the risks and challenges, the team members took the initiative to turn crises into opportunities, working with the Sudanese people to help each other and overcome difficulties together.  Members of the 36th batch of the Chinese medical assistance team to Sudan pose for a group photo in front of the headquarters of the team. (Provided by the medical team)  Members of the 36th batch of the Chinese medical assistance team to Sudan pose for a group photo in front of Abu Asher Hospital. (Provided by the medical team)  A doctor from the 36th batch of the Chinese medical assistance team to Sudan heads to the China-Sudan Friendship Hospital in Omdurman. (Provided by the medical team)  A chinese doctor from the 36th batch of the Chinese medical assistance team to Sudan embraces two newborn babies. (Provided by the medical team)  Two Chinese doctors from the 36th batch of the Chinese medical assistance team to Sudan take a group photo with local medical staff at the interval between surgical operations. (Provided by the medical team)â– 